[30;1m2 | [0m[35mThe primary intent of a two-tier system is to make cache invalidation more efficient,[0m
[30;1m3 | [0m[35mbecause the cache keys are typically tuples such as (project_id, time_interval, ...),[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35mbut we need to invalidate subsets of keys, e.g. all those associated with a[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mspecific project, very frequently (i.e. essentially at each span insertion). In a[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35msingle-tier system we would need to check all the keys to see if they are in the[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35msubset that we want to invalidate.[0m
